Step 1. Calculate the Debt-to-Asset Ratio.
• Total Assets (End_amount) = 19,501,451.49
• Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity – Total Owner's Equity 
  = 19,501,451.49 – 16,111,731.83 
  = 3,389,719.66
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 3,389,719.66 / 19,501,451.49 ≈ 0.1738 → "0.17"

Step 2. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit = 287,062.51  
• Total Revenue = 791,992.51  
• Gross Profit Margin = (287,062.51 / 791,992.51) × 100 ≈ 36.27% → "36.27%"

Step 3. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –4,504,752.68  
• Total Current Liabilities = 3,389,719.66  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = –4,504,752.68 / 3,389,719.66 ≈ –1.327, which rounds to –1.33 → "-1.33"

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.17",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.27%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.33"
  }
}
